The Coastal Pacific Food Distributors facility utilizes anhydrous ammonia as a heat transfer fluid in the plant refrigeration system.  The system is a single-stage mechanical refrigeration system that utilizes a flooded liquid evaporator feed.  The 0 A?F freezer operates 11 hours per day, the 36 A?F cooler operates 18 hours per day, and the 36 A?F refrigerated dock operates 24 hours per day.

The primary system components include:

? Two (2) High-Temperature Screw Compressors;
? Two (2) Low-Temperature Screw Compressors;
? Two (2) Evaporative Condensers;
? One (1) High-Pressure Receiver;

? One (1) High-Temperature Recirculator Package;
? One (1) Low-Temperature Recirculator Package;
? Four (4) Ammonia Pumps (two at each recirculator package); and
? Seventeen (17) Evaporators

Additional system components include:

? Oil Pots (one each at each liquid recirculator package for draining oil);
? Automatic Purger (with a foul gas tap at the evaporative condensers and a tap on the high pressure liquid line from the high pressure receiver and the liquid recirculation packages);
? One (1) Floor-Warming Heat Exchanger using glycol as the heat transfer fluid; and,
? Interconnecting Piping and Control Valves.

Safety systems include:

? Pressure relief valves on all pressure vessels in the system;
? Ammonia diffusion tank, 15,600 gallon capacity (all relief valve discharge lines lead to the diffusion tank for mixing with water in the event of a release from a component relief valve);
? Fire dump valve arrangement in ammonia diffusion panel for use by the fire department in the event of an emergency;
? Compressor safety cutouts and control panels to shut down the compressor operation if safe operating conditions are exceeded;
? Liquid level float switches;
? High level vessel alarms;
? Dual hot-gas solenoid valves;
? PLC alarm notification;
? Ventilation system for continuous and emergency ventilation;
? Emergency Control Station with emergency ventilation fan switch and emergency shutdown switch;
? Ammonia detection and alarm system for response to elevated levels of ammonia vapor in the cooling, freezer, and storage areas.  Detection will trigger the emergency ventilation system, emergency shutdown, and audible/visual alarms at preset levels;
? Spring-loaded, self-closing oil drain valves;
